The paper discusses the use of machine learning models (such as MLP) and Bayesian rules for predicting solar radiation. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with stochastic models, which could fall under the categories of statistical learning (cs.SI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of these models for stabilizing the electrical distribution grid, which could fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
